aa(lp23
VBut going to this camp,
p24
aVI was further shocked to realize that it was actually really fun.
p25
aVThey talked very little about politics.
p26
aVIt was mostly learning how to ride horses,
p27
aVshooting a bow and arrow,
p28
aVlive music at night,
p29
aVfree food and alcohol,
p30
aValso some air-gun target practice
p31
aVusing mainstream politicians' faces as targets.
p32
aVAnd this seemed like a very, actually, friendly, inclusive group
p33
aVuntil you started talking or mentioning anything to do with the Roma population,
p34
aVJewish people or immigrants,
p35
aVand then the discourse would become very hate-based very quickly.
